{
  "bookId": "laozi-heshanggong-wiki",
  "num": 25,
  "title": "第二十五章（象元）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "有物混成，先天地生。"
    },
    {
      "text": "寂兮寥兮，獨立而不改，"
    },
    {
      "text": "周行而不殆，"
    },
    {
      "text": "可以為天下母。"
    },
    {
      "text": "吾不知其名，字之曰道，"
    },
    {
      "text": "強為之名曰大。"
    },
    {
      "text": "大曰逝，"
    },
    {
      "text": "逝曰遠，"
    },
    {
      "text": "遠曰反。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故道大，天大，地大，王亦大。"
    },
    {
      "text": "域中有四大，"
    },
    {
      "text": "而王居其一焉。"
    },
    {
      "text": "人法地，"
    },
    {
      "text": "地法天，"
    },
    {
      "text": "天法道，"
    },
    {
      "text": "道法自然。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂道無形，混沌而成萬物，乃在天地之前。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "寂者，無音聲。寥者，空無形。獨立者，無匹雙。不改者，化有常。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道通行天地，無所不入，在陽不焦，託蔭不腐，無不貫穿，而不危怠也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道育養萬物精氣，如母之養子。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "我不見道之形容，不知當何以名之，見萬物皆從道所生，故字之曰道。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不知其名，強曰大者，高而無上，羅而無外，無不包容，故曰大也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "其為大，非若天常在上，非若地常在下，乃復逝去，無常處所也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言遠者，窮乎無窮，布氣天地，無所不通也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言其遠不越絕，乃復反在人身也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道大者，包羅天地，無所不容也。天大者，無所不蓋也。地大者，無所不載也。王大者，無所不制也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 10,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "四大，道、天、地、王也。凡有稱有名，則非其極也。言道則有所由，有所由然後謂之為道，然則是道稱中之大也，不若無稱之大也，無稱不可而得為名，曰域也。天地王皆在乎無稱之內也，故曰域中有四大者也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 11,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "八極之內有四大，王居其一也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-13",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 12,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人當法地安靜和柔也，種之得五穀，掘之得甘泉，勞而不怨也，有功而不置也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-14",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 13,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天澹泊不動，施而不求報，生長萬物，無所收取。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-15",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 14,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道清靜不言，陰行精氣，萬物自成也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-16",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 15,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道性自然，無所法也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
